17/02/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Romania's Supreme Defence Council (CSAT) confirmed on Saturday (February 16th) that it supports the NATO accession of Albania, Macedonia and Croatia. The Council also approved the accession of Ukraine and Georgia into the NATO Membership Action Plan. Romania, which joined NATO in 2004, will host the Alliance's two-day summit to be held in Bucharest starting April 2nd. The CSAT also adopted the Security Concept for the April summit and reviewed the political agenda of the event, particularly topics such as the situation in Afghanistan, the expansion of NATO and relations with its partner states. (AFP, Makfax, Rompres - 16/02/08)
